
Overview of noun harness

The noun harness has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (2) harness -- (a support consisting of an arrangement of straps for holding something to the body (especially one supporting a person suspended from a parachute))
2. (1) harness -- (stable gear consisting of an arrangement of leather straps fitted to a draft animal so that it can be attached to and pull a cart)

